title: NASA to Provide Update on DART, World’s First Planetary Defense Test
summary: NASA will host a media briefing at 2 p.m. EDT, Tuesday, Oct. 11, to discuss the agency’s Double Asteroid Redirection Test (DART) mission and its intentional collision with its target asteroid, Dimorphos.

title: Eutelsat says satellite jammers within Iran are disrupting foreign channels
summary: Signals originating within Iran have been jamming two Eutelsat satellites that provide foreign broadcasts in the country since Sept. 26, the French operator said Oct. 7.

title: Rocket Lab launches Argos tracking payload
summary: A Rocket Lab Electron rocket launched a satellite Oct. 7 carrying a payload for U.S. and French government agencies that will track wildlife and collect other sensor data.

title: NASA's InSight Waits Out Dust Storm
summary: InSight’s team is taking steps to help the solar-powered lander continue operating for as long as possible.

title: Rocket Lab launches “It Argos Up From Here” mission
summary: Rocket Lab has launched its 31st Electron rocket on the “It Argos Up From Here” mission from Rocket Lab’s private Launch Complex 1B (LC-1B), on the Mahia Peninsula in New Zealand. Liftoff occurred on Saturday, Oct. 8 at 6:09 AM NZT (17:09 UTC on Oct. 7).

title: Ariane 6 upper stage testing underway
summary: ArianeGroup has started static-fire tests of the upper stage of the Ariane 6 rocket, a key step in the development of the vehicle whose first launch remains uncertain.

title: Rocket Report: Falcon Heavy launch on tap; South Korea seeks Russia alternative
summary: Also, the Ariane 6 rocket is inching closer to the launch pad.

title: AFRL developing ‘cyber range’ for space operators
summary: AFRL is developing a cyber training range where Space Force operators could practice defending satellites using actual spacecraft in orbit

title: India on track for OneWeb launch in second half of October
summary: India expects to conduct the first launch of OneWeb satellites in eight months during the second half of October, Indian space agency ISRO said Oct. 5.

title: York Space wins $200 million Space Development Agency contract for 12 satellites
summary: York Space won a $200 million contract for the Space Development Agency's Tranche 1 Demonstration and Experimentation System (T1DES) program
